      "caption_text": "Figure 1: The basic method we use to \ufb01nd the intersection of a ray and a parametric object shown in a 2D example. Left: The ray is tested against a series of axis-aligned bounding boxes. Right: For each box hit an initial guess is generated in the parametric interval the box bounds. Root \ufb01nding is then iteratively applied until a convergence or a divergence criterion is met.",
